[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Check the Yesod book and libraries signatures.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Monadic forms permit free form layout and better treatment of hiddenField members.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] The types shown correspond to an older version, but the philosophy remains.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] The Handler monad returns content in one or more of several formats as components of types that implement the HasReps class {RepHtml, RepJson, RepXml, RepPlain, the dual RepHtmlJson, a pair or list of pairs `[(ContentType, Content)]`, ..}.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] The HasReps default implementation of chooseRep chooses the document representation to be returned according to the preferred content-type list of the client accept header.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] A Widget monad, based on a Writer one and argument to defaultLayout, facilitate to piece the widgets together.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Automatic closing tags are generated only for the tag at line start position.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Using non-English text in expressions requires use of the Unicode-aware type Text, since the Glasgow Haskell Compiler's (GHC's) show for the type String renders non-ASCII characters as escaped numerical codes.
