[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Keter is a process as a service that handles deployment and restart of Yesod web app servers, and, per *web app*, database creation for PostgreSQL.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] The console command `yesod keter` packs the web app. as a keter bundle for uploading to a keter folder named "incoming".
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Keter monitors the "incoming" folder and unpacks the app. to a temporary one, then assigns the web app a port to listen to, and starts it.
[src:yesod-haskell/yesod-web-framework] Initially it worked with Nginx as reverse proxy (keter version 0.1*), adding virtual server entries to its configuration and making Nginx reload it, but now Keter itself provides its own *reverse proxy* functionality, removing Nginx dependency and acting as the main web server.
